author: wn.com
title: Political, constitutional squabbling could decide next government
text: It could all come down to a mix of hard and fast rules, procedural convention and intense political manoeuvring. And with no party in clear striking distance of winning a majority government, there's much speculation about the scenarios that could ultimately pick the next prime minister and the party — or parties — that form government. ...
